long_desc.thetext:
If you're interested in a more concise example that doesn't involve multiple files, this appears to hit the same bug in a single file:

package bug;

public class AbstractNode {
	interface ExtendedNode {
	}

	interface CopyableNode<T extends ExtendedNode> {
	}

	ExtendedNode parent;

	AbstractNode(final ExtendedNode initialParent) {
		parent = initialParent;
	}

	public void method() {
		final CopyableNode<ExtendedNode> unused = (CopyableNode<ExtendedNode>) parent;
	}
}

Add @NonNullByDefault to package-info.java, and the error should appear on CopyableNode<ExtendedNode>. Strangely enough, setting unused to null doesn't seem to trigger an error, although this could be because the null analysis module stops on the ExtendedNode error and doesn't analyze far enough.
